willies
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:in NZ as elsewhere constr. THE WILLIES, esp. in the GET/GIVE THE WILLIES, the shakes (from terror, drink, fever, etc.) but esp. from fright or fearful anticipation
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: In OED from 1896 and long known in NZ OEDS US 1900; anglicised ca1925; WF n. pl. since ca1895 so P8 [OMIT??]
